I am single, have been for roughly three years (save for series of dates here and there, but nothing official), and have recently come to terms with it.

So really, I think it just means I need to make sure I'm comfortable with me so I can get to a point where I'm willing to open up to someone else. As it stands right now, I like my solitude and freedom a lot. I was about to write that I like them "too much," but I've come to realize I shouldn't feel guilty about how I am right now.
